doc.after: Rocket engine nozzles are surprisingly efficient heat engines for generating a high speed jet as a consequence of the high combustion temperature and high compression ratio Rocket nozzles give an excellent approximation to adiabatic expansion which is a reversible process and hence they give efficiencies which are very close to that of the Carnot cycle Given the temperatures reached over 60 efficiency can be achieved with chemical rockets
